{"prompt": "Build a website for a poetry review journal. The theme should be reflective and incorporate a mellow yellow.", "code": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>The Mellow Muse - Poetry Review Journal</title>\n    <style>\n        :root {\n            --primary-color: #FDEBD0; /* Mellow Yellow */\n            --secondary-color: #FFF8E1; /* Lighter shade of yellow */\n            --text-color: #333333;\n            --header-text-color: #4E443A;\n            --border-color: #D4AC00;\n        }\n        body {\n            font-family: 'Georgia', serif;\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n            background-color: var(--primary-color);\n            color: var(--text-color);\n            line-height: 1.6;\n        }\n        .container {\n            width: 80%;\n            margin: 20px auto;\n            background-color: var(--secondary-color);\n            padding: 30px;\n            border-radius: 10px;\n            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n        }\n        header {\n            background-color: var(--primary-color);\n            color: var(--header-text-color);\n            padding: 20px 0;\n            text-align: center;\n            border-bottom: 3px solid var(--border-color);\n            margin-bottom: 30px;\n        }\n        header h1 {\n            margin: 0;\n            font-size: 2.5em;\n            letter-spacing: 2px;\n        }\n        header p {\n            font-style: italic;\n            color: #666;\n        }\n        h2 {\n            color: var(--header-text-color);\n            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-color);\n            padding-bottom: 5px;\n            margin-top: 30px;\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\n        }\n        .poem {\n            margin-bottom: 30px;\n            padding-left: 20px;\n            border-left: 4px solid var(--border-color);\n        }\n        .poem h3 {\n            color: var(--header-text-color);\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\n        }\n        .poem p {\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\n        }\n        footer {\n            text-align: center;\n            padding: 20px;\n            margin-top: 40px;\n            background-color: var(--primary-color);\n            color: #666;\n            font-size: 0.9em;\n            border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);\n        }\n        a {\n            color: var(--header-text-color);\n            text-decoration: none;\n        }\n        a:hover {\n            text-decoration: underline;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n    <header>\n        <h1>The Mellow Muse</h1>\n        <p>A Journal of Reflective Poetry</p>\n    </header>\n\n    <div class=\"container\">\n\n        <h2>Featured Poems</h2>\n\n        <div class=\"poem\">\n            <h3>Whispers of Dawn</h3>\n            <p>\n                The sun, a painter's gentle hand,<br>\n                Strokes amber hues across the land.<br>\n                A quiet peace begins to bloom,<br>\n                Chasing away the lingering gloom.\n            </p>\n            <p><em>By Elara Vance</em></p>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"poem\">\n            <h3>Beneath the Willow</h3>\n            <p>\n                Ancient branches, softly sigh,<br>\n                As gentle breezes wander by.<br>\n                Here, thoughts like fallen leaves collect,<br>\n                Moments cherished, recollected.\n            </p>\n            <p><em>By Silas Thorne</em></p>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"poem\">\n            <h3>Golden Hour's Embrace</h3>\n            <p>\n                When day surrenders to the night,<br>\n                And bathes the world in softest light.<br>\n                A time for dreams to softly gleam,<br>\n                Caught in this hazy, mellow stream.\n            </p>\n            <p><em>By Luna Meadow</em></p>\n        </div>\n\n        <h2>About Us</h2>\n        <p>\n            The Mellow Muse is dedicated to showcasing poetry that evokes introspection, calm, and a gentle appreciation for the world around us. We believe in the power of words to create moments of quiet reflection and solace.\n        </p>\n\n        <h2>Submissions</h2>\n        <p>\n            We welcome submissions of original poetry that aligns with our theme of reflection and serenity. Please visit our <a href=\"#\">Submissions Page</a> for guidelines.\n        </p>\n\n    </div>\n\n    <footer>\n        <p>&copy; 2023 The Mellow Muse. All rights reserved.</p>\n    </footer>\n\n</body>\n</html>\n"}